      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i get that it can be both, but looking at history, it feels like the \"dangerous\" side usually wins out. like, most of the big wars and stuff come from nationalist movements. isn't it more accurate to say that nationalism is inherently a step toward conflict rather than just a tool that can be used \"well\"?",
