    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a pretty strong way to put it. so you're saying it's basically fundamentally flawed because it prioritizes group identity over human rights? if that's the case, can we even call it a \"tool for cohesion\" anymore, or is it just a built-in trap for society?",
